President Xu Shichang has asked me to tell you all

4
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:15,120
that the feelings and wishes of the government of the Republic of China and the Qingdao citizens

5
00:00:11,404 --> 00:00:13,988
[Wang Daxie, styled Botang, Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Republic of China]

6
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:16,880
are the same.

7
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:18,480
The government delegation of the Republic of China

8
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:20,320
attending the Paris Peace Conference

9
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:22,320
has successfully arrived in Paris.

10
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:25,040
They will discuss and solve

11
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:26,880
the relations and interests between China and Germany after the war

12
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:29,760
with the victorious countries,

13
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:33,120
to safeguard China's sovereignty and the interests of the people.

14
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,640
The ambassadors to the United States, Britain, France and Italy,

15
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,000
asked me to send greetings to you all

16
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:40,240
when they heard about this.

17
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:43,280
They will uphold the principle of fairness and justice,

18
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,520
safeguard China's sovereignty,

19
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:48,640
guarantee the territorial integrity of big and small countries

20
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,240
and their political independence.

21
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:51,920
So we have reason to believe

22
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,360
that in the near future,

23
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:57,040
the Shandong Peninsula will be completely returned to China.

24
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,760
Hurrah!

25
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,440
Because

26
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,680
we are, after all,

27
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,760
victorious in this world war.

28
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:13,760
We have a chance to claim the fruits of victory.

29
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:16,640
Long live China! Long live China!

30
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:25,840
Long live China! Long live China! Long live China!

31
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:33,600
On the verge of success,

32
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:36,400
the fact that

33
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:39,200
Cai Yuanpei and Chen Duxiu had made such a mess,

34
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,880
is really exploitative and pervasive.

35
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,680
Didn't the National Assembly already accept

36
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,200
Cai Yuanpei's proposal before?

37
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,880
Why did you retract it?

38
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,600
It wasn't the petition group that caused it.

39
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,160
Because the war in Europe was won,

40
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:57,440
the patriotic enthusiasm of Chinese people is unprecedentedly high.

41
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:01,120
Now there's another Qingdao petition group

42
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:04,480
that immediately won the support of the people.

43
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,400
And the Northern and Southern governments being at odds

44
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,360
has always been complained of by the people.

45
00:02:09,760 --> 00:02:12,240
It's very difficult to get a Paris Peace Conference,

46
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,680
which can divert your attention.

47
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,000
At this juncture,

48
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,080
naturally, there will be no more trouble.

49
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,080
This is not a retraction.

50
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:23,440
These people are really cunning.

51
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:26,560
Uncle, what should we do next?

52
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,320
You're at Peking University every day,

53
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,520
and you didn't notice

54
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,520
what their new trends are?

55
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,040
There's one thing.

56
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,200
Jinwan,

57
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,200
go to that house.

58
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:57,040
Uncle, Cai Yuanpei and Chen Duxiu have taken the lead recently

59
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,960
to set up a Work-Study Mutual Aid Society

60
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,120
that's said to experiment with anarchism

61
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,080
and communism,

62
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,600
and also open to the community

63
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:06,080
to enlist many people

64
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,600
who come from afar.

65
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,360
Mutual aid society...

66
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,880
Communism...

67
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,120
Go back to school.

68
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,280
Keep an eye on this mutual aid society.

69
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:33,200
Do you think there are articles to write here?

70
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:37,280
This kind of corrupt and filthy society

71
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:40,000
has the responsibility and obligation

72
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:44,800
to expose its true face to the public.

73
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,640
Yes, I understand.

74
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,360
Come and sit, one and all!

75
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,200
I'm in a really good mood today.

76
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:55,600
You say one thing and I say another, helping each other is the truth.

77
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,280
Come on, come on, sit down

78
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,200
Come and listen to Yannian

79
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,040
speak.

80
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,040
Students, take some stools.

81
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,240
Let's sit down.

82
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,680
Let's have a formal meeting today.

83
00:04:11,197 --> 00:04:14,158
[Chen Yannian, eldest son of Chen Duxiu]

84
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:12,720
Students,

85
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,120
today is a memorable day.

86
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,880
The first experimental group

87
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,880
of the Beijing Work-Study Mutual Aid Society is born.

88
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:25,200
Students, from now on,

89
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,240
the thirteen of us

90
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,160
are all members of a big family.

91
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,320
Everyone in the society calls each other comrades.

92
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,760
Do you have any objection?

93
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:32,560
Agreed.

94
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,840
Agreed, agreed, agreed.

95
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,040
Starting from today,

96
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:35,760
we are

97
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,440
comrades with common ideals and beliefs.

98
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,480
All right, comrades.

99
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,520
Let's introduce ourselves to each other first.

100
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,640
Who comes first?

101
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,240
I'll go first.

102
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,040
Go ahead.

103
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,320
Hello, comrades. My name is Shi Cuntong.

104
00:04:50,269 --> 00:04:52,630
[Shi Cuntong, Student at Zhejiang First Provincial Normal School]

105
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,520
I'm from Jinhua County in Zhejiang.

106
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:52,720
Born in 1899.

107
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,800
I'm a student at Zhejiang First Provincial Normal School.

108
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,000
The reason why I came to Beijing

109
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,200
to join our Work-Study Mutual Aid Society

110
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,400
is because I yearn for,

111
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,080
I yearn for a kind of anarchy

112
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,840
with no power, no law,

113
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:03,600
no religion, no marriage,

114
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,440
an ideal life without family.

115
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,360
And I think our Work-Study Mutual Aid Society

116
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:08,480
is this kind of life.

117
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,720
I understand the so-called work-study mutual aid

118
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,320
is labor

119
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:13,360
and hard work,

120
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,880
and mutual aid is evolution.

121
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:17,520
Our members work hard,

122
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,680
work all their lives, and study all their lives.

123
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,200
What a joy!

124
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,440
I hereby swear to all comrades,

125
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,640
that from this day onwards

126
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,480
I am the society and the society is me.

127
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:27,840
The interests of the society

128
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,520
is thus my personal interest.

129
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,640
Hurrah!

130
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,720
Hello, comrades. My name is Yu Xiusong.

131
00:05:36,606 --> 00:05:39,224
[Yu Xiusong, Student at Zhejiang First Provincial Normal School]

132
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,000
I'm from Zhuji County in Zhejiang.

133
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,280
Born in 1899.

134
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,640
Like Shi Cuntong,

135
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,480
I am a student at Zhejiang First Provincial Normal School.

136
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,760
Yesterday I wrote

137
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,720
a long letter to my parents

138
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,000
in which I explained in detail

139
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:46,960
why I came to Beijing

140
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,480
and the reasons for joining the Work-Study Mutual Aid Society,

141
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,520
which mentions

142
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:50,480
that my purpose

143
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,160
is to experiment with my ideal life

144
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,080
and spread it to all mankind

145
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,000
so that they can enjoy this new life

146
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,720
of happiness, love, mutual aid, and freedom

147
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,680
together!

148
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,960
Hurrah!

149
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,320
Hello, everybody!

150
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,960
My name is He Mengxiong. I'm from Lingxian County in Hunan.

151
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:06,991
[He Mengxiong, Visiting student at Peking University]

152
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,120
Born in 1898.

153
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,040
Now I'm studying in at the French Language Institute

154
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,640
and attending Peking University at the same time.

155
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,320
I want to join a mutual aid society

156
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,160
because I want to try a new life.

157
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,440
I have no other desires.

158
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,040
Exactly! Me too!

159
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,000
Sorry for being too rash.

160
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,800
Hello, comrades. My name is Yi Qunxian.

161
00:06:22,795 --> 00:06:25,318
[Yi Qunxian]

162
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,360
I ran out because I opposed my parents' forced marriage.

163
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:28,320
I'm here for the same reason as Comrade He,

164
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:31,520
that is to want to live a free and open life.

165
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,360
Nothing?

166
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:43,600
Okay, this is the notebook of our mutual aid society.

167
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,520
Let's pass it on and talk about it.

168
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,480
How many are there?

169
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,440
Six people.

170
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,080
Here.

171
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,040
Comrades,

172
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,360
the first experimental group of our Work-Study Mutual Aid Society

173
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:57,440
will officially open tomorrow.

174
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,760
The small courtyard on the west side of the entrance of the French study hall

175
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,960
has already been rented by us.

176
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:01,840
A few houses in the back

177
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,520
will be a dormitory for non-local members.

178
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,120
The front rooms facing the street

179
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,400
will be used as a canteen.

180
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,800
Work-study and public ownership of property.

181
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,320
Bai Lan,

182
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,520
announce our financial status

183
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,640
to everyone.

184
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:13,760
Ok.

185
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,760
The initial funds are all here now.

186
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:16,800
Let me show you.

187
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,840
It's 523 yuan in total.

188
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,200
Of this amount,

189
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,600
350 yuan is donated by the community.

190
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,680
Membership fees and donations by members

191
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,120
totals 173 yuan.

192
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,320
Regarding working, let me explain it first.

193
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:41,680
I, Qiaonian, and Guo

194
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,600
will be doing distribution for "New Youth".

195
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,440
Bai Lan will work as a tutor in the embassy district.

196
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,560
Keep doing all this.

197
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,920
It's just that revenue must be collectively owned.

198
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,240
Now, we will implement three businesses.

199
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:52,400
First, a work-study canteen that needs six people.

200
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,640
Second, four people to wash clothes.

201
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:56,640
Third, three people to show movies.

202
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:57,840
Let's discuss

203
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,200
these three businesses.

204
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:00,960
No need to discuss.

205
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:02,240
I'll run the canteen.

206
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,840
Xingang. Yannian.

207
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:04,800
Bai Lan. Liu Mei.

208
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,560
If you guys have nothing to do at times,

209
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,920
just come and assist me.

210
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:08,960
OK. No problem.

211
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,160
No problem. I'll tell you what,

212
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,840
Qingdao will be back soon.

213
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,000
I'm in a good mood these past two days.

214
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,120
Don't say that I'll "assist" you,

215
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,640
it sounds like I'd be a servant.

216
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:20,240
Then I'll do the laundry.

217
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,600
Count me in!

218
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:22,720
Count me in too.

219
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,760
Count me in too.

220
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,480
Good!

221
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:26,080
I'm good for nothing.

222
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,440
I'll play the movies.

223
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,840
What do you mean you're good for nothing? That's easy.

224
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,920
You're a good-for-nothing.

225
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,440
Joined the mutual aid society.

226
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,840
Showing movies is too hard for you.

227
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,360
You really are a good-for-nothing.

228
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:41,200
Great!

229
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:42,880
Well said!

230
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:43,840
Awesome!

231
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:44,880
Good point!

232
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:01,120
Ok, everyone is sleeping well.

233
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:02,880
Stop sleeping!

234
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:03,680
Stop sleeping!

235
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:03,920
Who is it?

236
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:04,640
Who are you?

237
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:05,520
Yu Xiusong!

238
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,050
Everyone, get up! You know what time it is?

239
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,320
I said what are you yelling about in the middle of the night?

240
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,280
Are you sleepwalking?

241
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,320
Middle of the night?

242
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,160
Still asleep, still asleep!

243
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:13,040
What are you doing?

244
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,960
Get up! Stop sleeping!

245
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,000
What are you calling for in the middle of the night?

246
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,480
Middle of the night? Do you know what time it is?

247
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,760
Do you know what day it is today?

248
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:20,560
What day?

249
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,680
Qiaonian, don't drag my blanket.

250
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,840
Today is the first day of the work-study canteen.

251
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:24,720
We buy rice at 6:30.

252
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,600
It's 6:00 now!

253
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,360
I almost missed something big.

254
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,400
Qiaonian! Wake up, wake up!

255
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,880
What's up? The chicken hasn't crowed yet.

256
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:34,960
What noise when it's dawn?

257
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:35,680
Wash yourself!

258
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,560
Get up quickly!

259
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,080
Where are you going?

260
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,760
I waited all night for their crowing.

261
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,280
I'll deal with them.

262
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,520
Guo, go and call the girls.

263
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,720
The girls?

264
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,160
The girls got up early to help.

265
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,160
You boys are worse than the girls.

266
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:55,360
Fools!

267
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,720
Come, come! Time to eat!

268
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,480
Come here.

269
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,520
Eat!

270
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,200
I almost got up late

271
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:10,880
because of you not crowing!

272
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,280
You didn't crow when you should've crowed!

273
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,880
Don't you know what your job is?

274
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,080
Comrades who got up late.

275
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,280
You guys can go back to sleep again.

276
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,960
I'll tell the sun

277
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,160
to come back out later.

278
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,520
We comrades who got up late

279
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,760
bow to the women who got up early.

280
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:27,520
No, don't, you don't have to.

281
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,120
Late risers,

282
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,640
why don't you go back to sleep?

283
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:31,920
We don't need you here.

284
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:32,480
Come on!

285
00:10:32,971 --> 00:10:33,991
I feel ashamed.

286
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,840
Late risers,

287
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,680
look at how beautifully the yard

288
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,280
and stove are cleaned

289
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:40,720
by the women who got up early

290
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,560
and Comrade Hai Wei who didn't sleep.

291
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,120
All thanks to our Shandong chef.

292
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,880
Late risers, go back to sleep.

293
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:52,560
Women who get up early don't feel tired when they work.

294
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,960
Comrade Yannian, listen carefully.

295
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,120
The frugal canteen opens today.

296
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,160
What was it again?

297
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,680
The best in China!

298
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:00,800
Yes, yes, yes!

299
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,680
Hurry up!

300
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:03,760
Come on!

301
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,240
Open for business!

302
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,120
Open up! Let's go!

303
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:09,840
Yes, yes, yes!

304
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,440
Good!

305
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:25,840
Is that OK?

306
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,440
Looks good!

307
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,200
Comrades,

308
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,840
the frugal canteen is our home.

309
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,520
Let's go, comrades!

310
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,640
Let's go!

311
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:35,520
Open up!

312
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,240
Let's work!

313
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,280
Let's go to work!

314
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,120
"Time flows like water,"

315
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:43,440
"Soon we shall depart from school,"

316
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:46,320
"We will ponder for a while"

317
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,880
"to understand today's homework,"

318
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:55,600
"Have we ever gone against our teacher?"

319
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,000
"Parents want children to come home,"

320
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:01,120
"We should not wander on the road"

321
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,840
"of leading the country's future and the world"

322
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:07,440
"which depends on our generation,"

323
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,920
"Everybody, let's work hard!"

324
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:14,160
"See you again tomorrow, classmates."

325
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:15,224
Let's go, everyone!

326
00:12:15,224 --> 00:12:17,040
Let's go!

327
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:20,400
Oil cakes! Steamed buns!

328
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,400
Freshly baked oil cakes!

329
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,240
Come and try it!

330
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,520
Yes, please try the oil cakes

331
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:26,240
and steamed buns!

332
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:27,360
Cheap and good quality.

333
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,200
Keep yelling, keep yelling.

334
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,800
We're selling breakfast here.

335
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,760
Morning, sir.

336
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,520
Come on, come on, students!

337
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,120
Our first order for today!

338
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:36,160
Welcome.

339
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:36,960
Hello, sir.

340
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:37,840
Hello, Mr. Shizhi.

341
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:38,800
Good morning, everyone.

342
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:40,240
Sir,

343
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,000
it's still hot just after coming out of the pot.

344
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:42,880
Please have one.

345
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,800
Mr. Shizhi, have some oil cakes and steamed buns.

346
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:45,840
It's cheap here.

347
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:46,445
Yes, try it.

348
00:12:46,445 --> 00:12:46,720
Try it.

349
00:12:48,554 --> 00:12:51,250
[Hu Shi, styled Shizhi, Professor at Peking University]

350
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,480
Okay, I'll have a taste.

351
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:55,840
Delicious!

352
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:56,160
Isn't it?

353
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:56,560
How is it?

354
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:57,840
Tastes good!

355
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:58,400
Isn't it?

356
00:12:58,960 --> 00:12:59,760
Try some more.

357
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:00,560
Try them all. Try them all.

358
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,640
I think we need to promote

359
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,240
our frugal canteen.

360
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:06,240
Find a newspaper to sponsor advertising.

361
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,400
Take a picture of the four words

362
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,160
and the couplet at the entrance and put it up.

363
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,440
That's your signature!

364
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,760
Right.

365
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:16,640
The four words on our plaque were written by Mr. Cai.

366
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:18,400
This couplet on both sides

367
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,520
was written by Mr. Lu Xun.

368
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,240
You see?

369
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,200
You didn't make good use

370
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,640
of such a good resource.

371
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:23,840
Isn't it a pity?

372
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,280
Good idea, sir.

373
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,040
Our student union can also help.

374
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,240
I'll have to trouble you then.

375
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:29,520
Everybody make good use of this resource.

376
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,720
Do you have steamed buns and oil cakes?

377
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:31,760
We do!

378
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,520
Mr. Shouchang!

379
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:34,800
Mr. Shouchang!

380
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:35,600
Students,

381
00:13:35,431 --> 00:13:37,491
[Li Dazhao, styled Shouchang, Director of Peking University Library]

382
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,520
your second order is here!

383
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,560
Shizhi, you also come to buy breakfast.

384
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:43,840
I'm not here to buy breakfast.

385
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,680
I am their volunteer publicist.

386
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,520
Mr. Shouchang,

387
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:48,640
today is the first day of opening

388
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:49,840
of our frugal canteen.

389
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,280
How can you support us?

390
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,800
I'm here to pay tribute.

391
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,440
This place is really nice.

392
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,800
Good, good.

393
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:58,560
Yannian,

394
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,240
an oil cake and a bowl of porridge.

395
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,280
Yes, sir, please sit down.

396
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:01,680
Okay.

397
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:02,720
An oil cake and a bowl of porridge!

398
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:03,280
Okay!

399
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:05,200
An oil cake and a bowl of porridge are not enough.

400
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,200
Mr. Shouchang is so big,

401
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,360
he needs to have three oil cakes and three bowls of porridge.

402
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:11,440
I can't eat so much.

403
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:12,880
How many oil cakes did you eat?

404
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:13,680
I have family rules.

405
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,200
I can't eat breakfast outside.

406
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:16,160
Do you have any money?

407
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:17,920
Yannian,

408
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,280
three oil cakes and three bowls of porridge.

409
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,400
I and Mr. Shizhi will eat here.

410
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,120
Mr. Shouchang.

411
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,080
Yannian!

412
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,760
No, family rules are family rules.

413
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:24,640
I can't break them.

414
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:25,360
You know what?

415
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,360
I'll tell your aunt Dongxiu tomorrow morning

416
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:28,560
to stop making breakfast.

417
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,960
Let's have breakfast together at the frugal canteen.

418
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:31,360
How about that?

419
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:31,880
Alright!

420
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:32,320
Okay!

421
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:33,920
I'm leaving, brother Shouchang.

422
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,080
Students, work hard!

423
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,040
See you later.

424
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:37,760
Goodbye, sir.

425
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,400
Sir, walk slowly.

426
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,160
Guo,

427
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:44,960
I'm leaving, too.

428
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,200
I will come again tomorrow.

429
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:48,640
I can give you the bill.

430
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:49,280
I'll pay later!

431
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,160
Come tomorrow.

432
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:50,880
See you tomorrow!

433
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:51,360
Come tomorrow.

434
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:55,520
The little fatty can eat quite well,

435
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,320
that fatty.

436
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:58,400
Yannian,

437
00:14:59,040 --> 00:14:59,760
come here.

438
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,360
Here is ten yuan for you.

439
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:04,720
I will come here for breakfast every day in the future.

440
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:05,600
This is inappropriate, sir.

441
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,360
All your money goes to the poor.

442
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:09,440
Don't listen to them.

443
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:12,080
Mr. Cai actually deducts thirty dollars a month

444
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,280
and sends it directly to my wife.

445
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,200
So I have no worries here.

446
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:16,880
You also don't have any ideas.

447
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:18,800
Thank you, sir.

448
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:20,720
It's really good.

449
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:23,760
Comrades!

450
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,080
The first official order,

451
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,280
ten yuan!

452
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:31,840
Business is booming!

453
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,280
Thank you, sir.

454
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,840
You say you're such a big man.

455
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:51,760
What are you angry with the children about?

456
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,200
I'm ashamed of you.

457
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:54,400
You can't talk nonsense.

458
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,160
I'm not angry with him.

459
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,240
You're not angry with them.

460
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:00,160
Why don't you let me go to the frugal canteen to buy breakfast?

461
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,280
Dad,

462
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,120
I also want to eat breakfast cooked by Yannian.

463
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,160
I want to eat, too.

464
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:07,514
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, Dean of Liberal Arts at Peking University]

465
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:05,840
Isn't there food at home?

466
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,360
Why do you want to buy it?

467
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,840
There is no place to spend money.

468
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:12,960
You said,

469
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,280
the frugal canteen opened on the first day today,

470
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,400
and I shouldn't have given them a boost.

471
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,480
You went today, will you go tomorrow?

472
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:21,600
Since it is an experiment, it needs objective facts.

473
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,440
The results are valuable.

474
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:24,800
Let them rely on themselves.

475
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,080
All right, let's eat.

476
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,440
Why are you going?

477
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:30,560
I filled all the porridge for you.

478
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:31,680
I'm full.

479
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:33,280
I'm going to have a look around

480
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,560
and digest the food.

481
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,040
Stop wiping.

482
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:01,200
This table is polished like a mirror.

483
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:04,560
There's not one guest here. Why are you cleaning it?

484
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,240
What's going on?

485
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:07,760
You can't sell a single oil cake.

486
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,160
Stop frying.

487
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:11,360
What's the use of frying so much?

488
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,120
There aren't any guests, it's a waste to fry.

489
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,760
Not how your words sound to my ears.

490
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:16,960
What is waste?

491
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:18,400
This cake won't sell.

492
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,320
There is something wrong with your publicity.

493
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,360
We've been dragging

494
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:22,240
people here all morning.

495
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,280
What are you talking about?

496
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,160
You made the oil cake. There is something wrong with it.

497
00:17:25,360 --> 00:17:27,040
I'm telling you, you have a skills problem.

498
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,320
I have a skills problem?

499
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:28,720
Yeah!

500
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,480
Mr. Hu Shi said my cake was delicious.

501
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,920
Then I don't think your cake is delicious.

502
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,120
Why don't you go out and get people?

503
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:35,360
A group of people have been sitting there all morning.

504
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,160
Guo was sleeping.

505
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:36,800
Why don't you go?

506
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:37,760
Okay, okay!

507
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,360
This is our first day of opening,

508
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:40,960
it's normal to have concerns.

509
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,320
Take your time, this thing can not be rushed.

510
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,760
Why do you have concerns?

511
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:44,720
Why don't you go?

512
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,240
Okay, okay, I won't argue with you all.

513
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:47,280
Do what you want.

514
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,080
What kind of attitude is that?

515
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:51,600
It's urgent.

516
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:52,400
Everyone.

517
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,560
Business is booming?

518
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,120
Hello, Mr. Zhongfu.

519
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:55,840
Hello, Mr. Zhongfu.

520
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:57,040
Please sit down, sir.

521
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:58,000
Please, please.

522
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:58,800
Please sit down, sir.

523
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:00,000
Make room for sir. Go, go, go.

524
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:01,200
Come here.

525
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:03,280
Sit down, sir.

526
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:08,800
Mr. Zhongfu,

527
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:09,920
you haven't had breakfast yet, have you?

528
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:12,000
No, no, no.

529
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:12,720
What can I get here?

530
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:13,680
What do you have here?

531
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:14,160
How many do we have here?

532
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:14,800
Don't serve him.

533
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:16,720
Why don't you serve him?

534
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:17,040
Yannian!

535
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,480
We don't need his sympathy.

536
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:19,760
Chen Yannian.

537
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:21,360
This is our business.

538
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,120
It's not up to you alone.

539
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:25,760
Sir, you're kidding.

540
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:26,880
Let me introduce to you what we have.

541
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,680
We have porridge, steamed buns, oil cakes

542
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:30,480
and soy milk.

543
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:31,280
And the soy milk

544
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,640
was freshly ground by me this morning.

545
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:35,520
Then I'll have a bowl of soy milk

546
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:36,800
and an oil cake.

547
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:37,760
Got it!

548
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:38,640
One is not enough.

549
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:41,200
Sir, Mr. Dazhao was here this morning.

550
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,880
He ordered three oil cakes

551
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:43,840
and three bowls of soy milk.

552
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:44,960
He eats so much!

553
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:45,520
Right.

554
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,560
Then give me two oil cakes

555
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,520
and one bowl of soy milk.

556
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:48,160
Got it!

557
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:48,800
Go, go!

558
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,000
Okay, okay, I'll go. I'll go

559
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:51,360
Please wait a moment, sir.

560
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,320
This is a fresh cake

561
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:58,000
Here is one cake, fresh out of the pan.

562
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,040
Not bad.

