602
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,760
I- I- I- Where would I go?

603
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:50,880
I don't know.

604
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,880
Look, have you eaten the oil cake?

605
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:53,600
Yeah.

606
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:54,400
Have you drunk soybean milk?

607
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:55,440
Just a sip.

608
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,640
Then a sip is a drink.

609
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:57,760
Isn't that freeloading?

610
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:58,800
What freeloading?

611
00:20:59,360 --> 00:20:59,840
Didn't I tell you?

612
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:01,840
I'll give you the money when I come back.

613
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:05,040
We absolutely cannot cancel the bill.

614
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:06,400
I've heard that.

615
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,920
Didn't Fu Sinian cancel the bill, too?

616
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,440
There's a difference between you and Fu Sinian.

617
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:10,640
How about you?

618
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:12,160
How much do you earn a month?

619
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:14,560
What should I do then?

620
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:15,840
I just forgot my money.

621
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,360
I forgot my money. Why?

622
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:18,720
Should I give you all my clothes?

623
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:19,520
No, no, no.

624
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:20,640
We can't take your clothes.

625
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,000
How about this?

626
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,520
We are an anarchist

627
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:25,040
communist mutual aid society

628
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,880
that follows the principle of mutual assistance.

629
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,160
Those who do not work, do not eat.

630
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:30,800
Go wash the dishes to settle the bill.

631
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:33,760
Wash the dishes?

632
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:37,200
That doesn't suit you?

633
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,920
Chopping firewood, washing clothes, feeding chickens,

634
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:41,680
milking goats, grinding soybeans,

635
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,280
and gluing envelopes.

636
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,720
Anything. You choose.

637
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:52,240
Okay, I'll wash the dishes.

638
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:53,920
Mr. Zhongfu, how can you wash the dishes?

639
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:54,880
No, no, no.

640
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:56,240
I will follow your rules.

641
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:57,840
A man without money is no man at all.

642
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:58,560
I'll wash the dishes.

643
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:00,080
Please eat first, then wash after eating.

644
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,520
I'll wash it before eating it.

645
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:02,880
Otherwise, I can't eat steadily.

646
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,000
Can you beat me? This

647
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,920
Where are your bowls?

648
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:07,680
I'm really sorry.

649
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,600
You haven't finished your meal yet.

650
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:11,440
You have to wash your own dishes after eating.

651
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,040
No, Yannian.

652
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:14,240
Chen Yannian

653
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:16,480
You're trying to squeeze your old man, aren't you?

654
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:17,920
Who pushed you?

655
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,240
Hello, madame.

656
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,680
You also

657
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,120
asked your dad to wash your dishes.

658
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,520
He hasn't smashed all your bowls yet.

659
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,080
I knew you didn't have any money.

660
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:32,560
Yannian, here.

661
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,480
This is the money your father gives you.

662
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:38,720
Comrades, the third order!

663
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:40,400
Thank you, guests.

664
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:42,080
Hold on to this.

665
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:43,840
Thank you, Mr. Zhongfu.

666
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:49,200
Didn't you have breakfast this morning?

667
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:54,160
Not full?

668
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,840
This morning,

669
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,440
I was the one who wanted to give you a boost first.

670
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:03,360
As a result, your father refused

671
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,720
to let me come anyway.

672
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:07,520
As a result, I came here first.

673
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:12,320
The point is, he didn't bring any money.

674
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,040
Liu Mei, Bai Lan.

675
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:18,800
I'm here for the first time today.

676
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:19,840
Show me around.

677
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:20,480
Ok.

678
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:23,600
This is our chicken and duck.

679
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:24,800
This is common property.

680
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:25,840
That's the laundry room.

681
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:27,840
Good, good, good.

682
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:11,120
You let go!

683
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:12,880
You let go!

684
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:13,680
You let go!

685
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:14,480
I won't let go!

686
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:15,280
If you join a mutual aid society,

687
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:16,720
you must have all communist consciousness.

688
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,240
This is my personal property. Why should I be communist?

689
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:18,960
You let go!

690
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:19,920
Will you let go?!

691
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:20,800
I won't let go!

692
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:21,680
Don't you let me shout?

693
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:22,480
Shout, then!

694
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:28,720
Yu Xiusong.

695
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,760
What are you doing? Let him go.

696
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,960
Comrade Chen Yannian, you're just in time.

697
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,320
You reason this out.

698
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:36,640
I was so excited to join a mutual aid society

699
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,160
to realize communism that I stayed up all night.

700
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:38,560
Get down.

701
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,520
I put all my clothes away.

702
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,240
Get down!

703
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,280
Now that we're communist,

704
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:45,040
there can be no more private property.

705
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,200
I laid out all the clothes I brought.

706
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:50,400
I think Comrade Yu is a rich boy.

707
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:52,800
I came to encourage him to put out his clothes.

708
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:54,240
There are three new pants here.

709
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,600
Guess what?

710
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:56,960
He refused.

711
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,480
How unreasonable are you?

712
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,080
Everyone, what are your thoughts on this?

713
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:01,600
She came to open my suitcase early in the morning

714
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:02,560
and asked me to hand in my clothes.

715
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:03,920
This suitcase is full of my personal belongings

716
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:04,960
and school equipment.

717
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,480
Yes, there are pants in it.

718
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,640
Those are men's pants. You can't even wear them!

719
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:10,160
You're so unreasonable!

720
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:11,760
Who said I was going to wear your pants?

721
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:13,760
I can't wear your pants.

722
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,520
But other comrades can wear it.

723
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:17,680
What's wrong with you?

724
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:19,120
You have three new pants here.

725
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:21,600
Can't you share with those whose pants are worn out?

726
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,440
Or to comrades with only one pair of pants?

727
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:25,680
You are still elected by the Social Committee.

728
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:26,960
Selfish!

729
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,080
I am selfish?

730
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,680
You're a pants person, aren't you?

731
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,200
You say "pants" left and "pants" right.

732
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:34,000
Who says communism must hand in pants?

733
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:36,240
Is there such a clause in the constitution of our Work-Study Mutual Aid Society?

734
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:37,520
All right, stop arguing.

735
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,440
Do you want to share the members' clothes?

736
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,120
There are no clear rules yet.

737
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:42,400
You have this idea?

738
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,760
It can be submitted to the general assembly for voting.

739
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,480
Until then, keep it as it is.

740
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:49,520
Time to eat.

741
00:25:59,040 --> 00:25:59,520
Chairman.

742
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:00,960
Minister Chen has arrived.

743
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:02,080
Master Bo.

744
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:04,240
What important documents?

745
00:26:04,560 --> 00:26:06,080
Minister Chen has to deliver it himself.

746
00:26:07,364 --> 00:26:08,727
[Chen Lu, styled Renxian, Acting Foreign Minister]

747
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:08,640
See for yourself.

748
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,960
What's going on here?

749
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,360
It's been rejected, and returned unchanged.

750
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:24,160
What's the matter?

751
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:27,520
Last night, Japan's envoy to China, Xiao Yun, met with me

752
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,120
and the envoys of the United States, Britain, Italy and France

753
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:32,640
and claimed that the core of the Shandong Peninsula issue

754
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,480
was not the interests of China and Germany,

755
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,400
but the interests of Japan and Germany.

756
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:39,200
We asked that at the Paris Peace Conference...

757
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:41,040
Don't make a big deal out of it.

758
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,200
Early this morning,

759
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:46,880
President Xu brought Wu Bingxiang and me together

760
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:47,920
and asked me

761
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:51,120
to return this petition

762
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:52,560
and the people's statement to you

763
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:55,040
He asked Wu Bingxiang to take measures.

764
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:58,400
No more slogans and leaflets appeared on the streets of Beijing.

765
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:01,840
Then the embassies of the United States, Britain, France and Italy

766
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:05,120
also returned all the invitation letters from Qingdao.

767
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:06,720
Outrageous.

768
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:09,360
Can spilled water be recovered?

769
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:11,760
What does Xu Shichang want?

770
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:13,760
He's playing with me like a monkey.

771
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,120
Don't you want Qingdao?

772
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,040
President Xu also asked me to tell you

773
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,120
that he still wants Qingdao,

774
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:21,440
we should pay attention to strategy.

775
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,120
Don't boil the Japanese.

776
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:25,120
If you can't bear it, you will make great plans.

777
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:26,720
He knows how to endure.

778
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:28,560
Be patient when you are defeated.

779
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:30,080
If you win, you have to endure it.

780
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:32,480
I think this country is possessed.

781
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:35,360
Weak countries have no diplomacy. This is an iron law.

782
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:36,480
Then what is justice?

783
00:27:38,560 --> 00:27:40,160
What about the embassies of the four countries?

784
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:43,040
Wilson's words don't count either?

785
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,760
When the U.S. Embassy returned the letter,

786
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:47,120
it emphasized

787
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,040
that the U.S. attitude towards China

788
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:50,720
has always been consistent.

789
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,600
I don't think so.

790
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,520
This is a signal

791
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:59,680
that the Paris Peace Conference is in trouble.

792
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:02,560
Master Bo, it already is.

793
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:04,160
What happened?

794
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:05,680
When the delegation received

795
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,120
the ranking of domestic personnel,

796
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,400
it was already in an uproar.

797
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:11,040
Wang Zhengting cursed President Xu.

798
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:12,640
for discriminating against the Southern government.

799
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,400
Shi Zhaoji took the load off his shoulders.

800
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,720
Lu Zhengxiang simply went to Switzerland.

801
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:20,640
Now it's all up to Gu Weijun.

802
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:22,240
This is to be expected.

803
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:23,920
I have sent telegrams to Lu Zhengxiang

804
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,280
and Gu Weijun respectively,

805
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:27,280
and Gu Weijun sends back replies daily.

806
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:30,560
When it's critical, Lu Zhengxiang must come out.

807
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,920
It's admirable that the chairman

808
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:35,280
has won a great victory.

809
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:46,000
There is still trouble at home.

810
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:49,200
Cao Rulin, Zhang Zongxiang, Lu Zongxing.

811
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:50,400
These people are despicable.

812
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:54,320
The pro-Japanese faction can't be underestimated.

813
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:57,280
After all is said,

814
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,520
all still depend on the foreigners.

815
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,480
Truly a shame!

816
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:29,440
Please.

817
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:32,720
This is recommended by Mr. Dazhao.

818
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:33,680
That's right.

819
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:34,960
Okay, sit down.

820
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:35,440
Thank you.

821
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,280
The Work-Study Mutual Aid Society

822
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:43,120
